<br>
Lets examine this closely for a moment.<br>
<br>
The situation, as it exists, is that of a gentleman's agreement. The first cleric is waiting, the second cleric is waiting for the first to leave. The only differance is that 3+ other clerics feel that they will not get a place in line if they also do not wait for others to finish. <br>
<br>
Would any suggest that clerics must leave the zone if they are not first or second in line? I would guess not, really. Would any suggest that if there are multiple clerics waiting, that the person assuming the number 2 position should be randomed between all the clerics waiting? (No, that is not a good idea). <br>
<br>
Quite frankly, the situation is this: Sure, the clerics who are in skyfire may hate the idea of waiting there for 5 weeks, but they are willing to do it, obviously, or they would not *be* there. <br>
<br>
The idea of only being on for 12 hours a day is nice, yes. Practical, no, definately not. <br>
<br>
In an ideal world, Ragefire would pop every 24 to 48 hours. Since he doesn't, we currently have the *only* real arrangement that even attempts some degree of fairness. <br>
<br>
In any event, I'm sure the &quot;tell me why it's retarded&quot; sentiment will come out some more, but yeah, it won't work. <br>
<br>
AFK clerics will not go away by any decisions we make. They will only be aided if Verant pulls their collective heads out of their @$$. Well, scratch that: the AFK clerics will go away if we make it a server wide FFA and people pray for the killing blow. But how much would that suck?<br>
<br>
Yeah, lots. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
